<?php die('Unauthorized access.'); ?>a:39:{s:2:"id";s:1:"8";s:4:"type";s:8:"document";s:11:"contentType";s:9:"text/html";s:9:"pagetitle";s:15:"Pastor's Corner";s:9:"longtitle";s:15:"Pastor's Corner";s:11:"description";s:37:"I am Pastor's little space on the web";s:5:"alias";s:6:"pastor";s:15:"link_attributes";s:0:"";s:9:"published";s:1:"1";s:8:"pub_date";s:1:"0";s:10:"unpub_date";s:1:"0";s:6:"parent";s:1:"1";s:8:"isfolder";s:1:"1";s:9:"introtext";s:0:"";s:7:"content";s:2977:"<p>
Mt. Zion Family and Friends, 
</p>
<blockquote>
</blockquote>
<p>Our <a href="http://mtzioncary.org/home/about_mtzion/vision.html" target="_blank">vision</a> to "Worship Christ, Spread the Gospel, and Serve the Community" has never been stronger.&nbsp; This year,
we want to take our faith back from complacency and self-focus to sacrificial living for Jesus Christ.&nbsp; Our 2011 church theme is "Radical".&nbsp; We have a Master who demands radical abandonment.&nbsp; We are to abandon everything to follow Jesus.&nbsp; He demands radical discipleship.&nbsp; We are called to make disciples of all nations.&nbsp; Jesus demands radical generosity.&nbsp; We are called to give generously, abundantly, and sacrificially.&nbsp; Jesus demands radical missions.&nbsp; We are called to go out into our local communities and into the nations to spread the Gospel. </p>
<p><img style="float: right;" title="Harris Family" src="assets/images/Harris%20Family.jpg" alt="Harris Family" width="420" height="279" /></p>
<p>
This year we embark on the <a href="http://radical.mtzioncary.org/" target="_blank">Radical Experiment</a>.&nbsp; </p>
<p>There are five parts to the experiment:<br /><br />1) Pray for the entire world.  Pray for specific needs among the nations. <br /><br />2)
 Read through the entire Word.  Get through the entirety of Scripture in
 one year.  <br /><br />3)
 Sacrifice money for a specific purpose.   We should put a cap on our 
spending so that we can give more.  Give to the church for ministry, 
give more to love offering, give toward mission trips, etc.<br /><br />4) 
Spend time in another context.  Whether it's overseas for a short term 
mission trip or the soup kitchen downtown, we must go and be with 
people who aren't like us.  We are planning two mission trips during 
2011: Ecuador and Haiti.<br /><br />5) Commit our lives to multiplying 
communities.  Be a part of a local church that is growing, making 
disciples and sending people out.  Serve faithfully and pray fervently 
for it.  And if you're not in a ministry, get into one.</p>
<p>Join us this year as we seek to be radical for Christ.&nbsp; Our lives are short and we do not have
time to waste on temporary things.&nbsp; We
must accomplish our mission of sharing the Good News of God&rsquo;s redemptive plan
to sinners.&nbsp; We must spend our lives in
pursuit of Christ and abandon the comforts of materialism.</p>
<p>Jesus Christ is worth every sacrifice and commitment.&nbsp; He is our
treasure.&nbsp; He is more valuable than
anything else we can have, and He is worth giving up and abandoning everything.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>
In HIS service, 
</p>
<p>
Pastor Harris and Family 
</p>
<p>
(Willie, Anita, Isaiah, Abigail, and Gabrielle) 
</p>
<p>
